element.name: G is for Golf by Hezekiah, Traditional Cache (1/1)

center.font: Visit the new Geocaching Ireland discussion forum HERE

element.long-description: G is also for "Garda" - and their golf club commands a spectacular view of the city. The cache is placed outside the grounds, which are private (spot the security cameras).
element.encoded-hints: At the foot of the pole marked "18"

ul.li:
2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by BlueFoxPL
Another great day for caching... found with some friends. TFTC.

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by colmyster
Second attempt at this one. Was disturbed by mugglers the first time. TFTC

2010-06-13T19:00:00Z : Found it by Wicca Cailín
Nice views from up here, not so many passing cars either. TFTC.

2010-03-27T19:00:00Z : Found it by Spark_ie
Quick grab, another one in the series! Cycle up that hill nearly killed me !! But managed to make it to the cache without stopping! Continued up the hill for a crackin downhill ride to the T for Traffic :) TFTC, Spark_ie

2010-03-13T20:00:00Z : Found it by Frezeluberz
Found quickly with no problems. TNLNSL. TFTC.

2009-07-19T19:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
Out for a day of caching with JME1979 - this was our seventh find for the day and my 304th overall. A very quick park and grab.
